1. e4 e5
{ Now, the main move by a very wide margin is Ng1-f3. I cannot remember ever facing another one in my own practice. But, other moves do exist. In this chapter, we will cover all of White's second move sidelines, from the romantic King's Gambit to the much more topical Bishop's Opening, and everything in between.   For the most part, we are still playing to equalize. A move like  2.Nc3  might not be the most challenging, but it develops a new piece to a reasonable square and we certainly cannot play for an edge just yet, but in a lot of the more aggressive lines, White can end up worse if he is not careful. }
