1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. c3
{ Now, while there is nothing wrong with taking on c3, I think that basically gives White what he wants. I like going a different direction. }
3... Qe7
{ It turns out to actually be very annoying to defend e4. Without Nc3 or Nd2, and Bd3 running into d5, what is White to do? }
4. cxd4
{ The machine wants to give up on equalizing material. This is understandable, but Black gets his pieces out pretty fast and I don't believe White gets enough compensation. }
4... Qxe4+ 5. Be3 Bb4+ 6. Nc3 Nf6
{ Black is ready to castle next and I find it hard to believe White can have enough for a pawn. }
