1. e4 e5 2. d3
{ 2.c3?!  d5!  Black is already a little better. The Center Game becomes a pretty good opening when the queen is immune to harassment from the b-knight! }
2... Nf6
{ Black is ready for d5 next, when the position will likely transpose to a reverse Philidor as we see in some of the @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppp1ppp/8/4p3/4P3/8/PPPP1PPP/RNBQKBNR w - - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  2.Nf3  Nc6  3.c3  lines. }
