1. e4 e5 2. d3
{ 2.c3?!  d5!  Black is already a little better. The Center Game becomes a pretty good opening when the queen is immune to harassment from the b-knight! }
2... Nf6
{ Black is ready for d5 next, when the position will likely transpose to a reverse Philidor as we see in some of the 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.c3 lines. }
3. f4 { This is the only attempt at independant value. } 3... exf4 4. Bxf4 Nc6
