4... Nd4 5. Nxd4 { This forces sterile equality right away. } 5... exd4 6. e5
{ Now after some captures, things become very equal very fast. } 6... dxc3 7.
exf6 Qxf6 8. dxc3 Qe5+
{ This is the easiest solution. White must trade queens, or lose time with his bishop. The position is very dry, and very equal. }
9. Qe2 Qxe2+
{ Black is ready for Bf8-c5 and O-O next, with d7-d5 to follow. The position is absolutely equal and a draw feels really likely, but it's not that hard to mess things up if one gets inattentive. We'll see Kramnik wina position like this one in the annotated games section. }
