Qxe4+ 9. Ne3 Bg4
{ Not a difficult move of course, but an important one all the same. } 10. Be2
Nxe2 11. Qxe2 O-O-O
{ Black's active pieces easily give him enough for the pawn. } 12. d3 Bxf3 13.
Qxf3 Qxf3 14. gxf3 Rhe8
{ Black is ready for Nd5 next, and White will not be able to effectively keep the e-file closed. The position is absolutely equal. }
