4... Nd4 5. Bc4 Bc5
{ It takes a little bit of bravery to play this move, but it basically forces a draw. }
6. Nxe5 Qe7 7. Nf3
{ Black is a pawn down, but he can play very energetically. } 7... d5 8. Bxd5
Bg4 { Now the game basically ends in a draw by force. } 9. d3 O-O-O
{ Nxd5 is a big threat, and castling hardly looks appealing, so White's move is forced. }
10. Be3 Nxd5 11. Nxd5 Rxd5 12. exd5 Re8 13. c3 Nxf3+ 14. gxf3
{ Now Black needs to be careful, as White plans to escape with his king via d2 and c2, remaining material up. But, a couple more accurate moves bring the game to a prompt end. }
14... Qh4 15. Kd2 { The only move to avoid mate, but now } 15... Rxe3
{ Forces an immediate draw. } 16. fxe3 Qf2+ 17. Kc1 Bxe3+ 18. Kb1 Bxf3 19. Qe1
Bxh1 20. Qxh1 Qe2 21. a4 Qxd3+ 22. Ka2 Qc4+
{ The game ends in perpetual check. This exact game has been played out several times. }
