1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4
{ Chapter 5 will cover the Scotch. This is a very ambitious opening for White, aiming to use his extra move at that start of the game to take a bigger stake in the center. }
3... exd4 4. Nxd4
{ White now has one pawn in the center against zero, but he is a little behind in development. If he can catch up and consolidate, he should be better. This is why I strongly believe Black should challenge the center right away. }
4... Nf6
{ White will have to take on c6 and push e4-e5 to avoid transposing to the Four Knights. We will see a lot of sharp and forcing lines as Black tries to make use of his lead in development and turn it into something tangible before he ultimately becomes worse for strategic reasons. This should be doable but there are a lot of sharp lines to memorize. }
*

