6... d5 7. exd5 cxd5 8. O-O Be7 9. c4 O-O 10. cxd5 Nxd5
{ With Bb7 coming next, Black's much more active pieces are easy enough to compensate for the slightly compromised queenside structure. White's knight on b1 will have a very hard time developing. }
