7... Nd5
{ This is the main tabiya of the Scotch. White's two main tries are the old move in  8.c4  and the trendy modern one with  8.h4  ,  but he also has some other move order tricks we should be ready for.   In general, the plan we want to execute is g7-g6, Bf8-g7, O-O and Re8. This will likely lead to the fall of the e5-pawn. Often we are meeting c2-c4 with Bc8-a6, gaining further time for our development. }
