18. Rab1 Qe8 { Now, f7-f6 is on the way. } 19. a3 { This is too ambitious. }
19... f6 20. b4 Bb6
{ fxe5 comes next, and White will either have to accept a butchered structure and possibly a lost f3-pawn, or if he takes back with the d-pawn, the bishop wakes up. White really would have liked to have gotten f3-f4 in to recapture with the f-pawn on e5, and here he is too slow to pull that off. }
