21. c4 { White needs to immediately get his queen back to the defense. } 21...
dxc4 22. Qf3
{ Now, allowing d4-d5 next is not to be recommended. Black should be very energetic. }
22... g5
{ Of course Black continues along with his main plan, and before White could dislodge the knight with d4-d5. }
23. Qg3 Qxg3+ 24. fxg3 gxf4 25. Bxf4 Rd8
{ The last tough move. From here, more or less everything should be fine. } 26.
Bh6 Rf7 27. Rab1
{ Now, finally on move 27, I want to offer an alternative to what Wesley covered. }
27... Nxd4
{ Wesley only covered Rxd4 here, which should be good enough for a draw as well, but I don't like abandoning the back rank and this seems much easier to me. Black has an easy regrouping available with c7-c5, Rf7-c7, and Kg8-e6 coming next. }
