8... dxe4 9. dxe4 Qd3 10. Bb2 a5
{ I like this direct move, aiming to take advantage of White's pushing for queenside play before he has castled. Furthermore, we get this move in before the queen can be forced to a6. }
11. Bc4
{ Rapport tried this in one of his two games to reach this position, but it's not too scary. }
11... Qd6
{ Taking advantage of no Nc4 possibilities. Bc4-b3-c4 in the last few moves does not impress. }
12. a3 Nd7
{ Black is ready to coordinate his pieces with Nd7-b6 and Bc8-e6, and someday White might regret making so many pawn moves on the queenside. The machine insists on absolute equality. }
