21. h4 { For unknown reasons, my computer suggests this is best. } 21... c6
{ Black is ready for Bb6-c7 next, conquering the f4-square. The machine's recommended choice of c3-c4 hardly looks human to me, but it does force the knight to move before f4 becomes a viable option. }
22. c4 Nb4 23. Bf4
{ Now, we see that c7-c6 made some weaknesses. The d6-square looks very tender, and our plan to play Bb6-c7 obviously fell on its face. Still, Black is fine here, but he does need to remember a couple important moves. }
23... Nc8
{ First, the knight overprotects d6. It looks like we are about to get our bishop marooned on a7... }
24. c5 Nd3 { This tactical resource saves the day. Black is fine. } *

