1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6
{ At long last, we are in the Berlin!   White has two main moves here in O-O and d2-d3, which have a combined total of five chapters between thr two of them. In this section, we will cover all of White's extraneous tries. Since Nb1-c3 would transpose to the 4 knights, there really is not much left.   It is a short chapter as it does not take much to disarm moves like Qd1-e2 or d2-d4. }
