{ White should not be allowed to push f4-f5, getting his pawns onto light squares to complement the dark squared bishop. }
13. Qe2 { Now things get pretty forced. } 13... O-O 14. Nf3 Bf6
{ Black should not allow his dark squared bishop to be exchanged. } 15. e5 Be7
16. Rd1 Qe8 17. Nd4 Qf7 18. Nxe6 Qxe6
{ The machines offer white a slight edge, but this is already a dead draw. Black can put a rook on d8, trade all the rooks if so inclined, stick his king on f7 and pawns on g6 and h5.   White has absolutely no way to even try to break through, and this is thanks in no small part to the horrible dark squared bishop basically being a piece of dead wood. Wesley So tried this for White twice, and got absolutely nowhere both times. }
