{ Of course, grabbing the pawn is a critical option that Black should be ready for. }
6... O-O 7. Bxc6 bxc6 8. d4
{ Now, the main move by far is Bc5-b6, and there are some concrete reasons that this makes sense, but I prefer to keep the bishop on a more active square. }
