5... d5 { I like striking in the center right away. } 6. exd5
{ This is the most critical move, and the recommendation of Nils Grandelius in his course here on Chessable. Black should be ready, but he is certainly fine. }
6... Qxd5 7. Bc4 Qd6 8. Nbd2
{ Nils' recommendation. This move has gained some popularity recently. } 8...
Bf5 9. b4 Bb6 10. Ng5 O-O 11. Nde4 Nxe4 12. dxe4 Qxd1+ 13. Kxd1
{ Nils clearly likes this line, as he played it against Vidit, and then recommended a slightly altered version in his course. Black needs to be careful here, but he is definitely fine. }
13... Bg4+
{ Provoking the pawn to f3 to deny a retreat square for the g5-knight. } 14. f3
Bd7 { h6 is coming. Now things get pretty forced. } 15. a4 h6 16. a5 hxg5 17.
Bxg5 { Now we need one last important move. } 17... Bxa5 18. bxa5 b6
{ Black is very solid and very fine. His knight is coming to a5 next, regardless of whether White exchanges off his a-pawn or not. }
