[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Ch. 10 - Berlin 4.O-O Sidelines"]
[Black "Berlin 4.O-O Sidelines: 5.d4 Nd6 with 6.a4"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. d4 Nd6
{ Now, White's main move by far is Bxc6, for obvious reasons. But, he does have a few miscellaneous options we should at least be ready for. }
6. a4
{ This has been seen a couple times, but it makes no sense to me. It looks like a bad version of 6.Ba4. }
6... e4 7. Re1 Be7 8. Ne5 O-O 9. Nc3 f6
{ Why not? This is exactly the kind of position where one has to wonder why the bishop is on b5 instead of a4. White cannot give a check on c4, and he cannot take c6 as dxc6 will come with tempo. }
10. Nc4 f5 11. d5 Ne8
{ I like this move, using tactical resources to solve the problem of the bad knight. Since white's knight on c4 cannot be exchanged on demand, taking c6 does not win a piece since the dumb bishop on c6 will be trapped. a7-a6 comes next and Black is better. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Ch. 10 - Berlin 4.O-O Sidelines"]
[Black "Berlin 4.O-O Sidelines: 5.d4 Nd6 with 6.Bxc6 #1"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. d4 Nd6
{ Now, White's main move by far is Bxc6, for obvious reasons. But, he does have a few miscellaneous options we should at least be ready for. }
6. Bxc6 dxc6 7. dxe5 Nf5 { This is White's last chance to avoid the endgame. }
8. Qe2
{ Of course the main move is to take on d8, but this has been tried recently by some strong guys. It is not totally without merit, as Rf1-d1 coming next could be a serious issue. Black should be ready. }
8... Nd4
{ The f5-knight is often a misplaced piece that Black should be trying to fix, and now he can exchange it off while also getting his queen to d4. She will have a lot of good squares available to her on the fourth rank to avoid harassment. }
9. Nxd4 Qxd4 10. Rd1
{ 10.Nc3?  Bg4!  Black is ready for O-O-O next, with a fantastic position. }
10... Qg4
{ Black is already better. Should the queens exchange, he will reach a standard looking Berlin Endgame where he is allowed to castle. }
11. f3 Qg6
{ Bf5 comes next and Black looks better thanks to his active bishop pair and powerful play on the light squares. }
