7... a6
{ First, we kick the bishop away from c6. Once Black plays d7-d5, the bishop would have been annoying. }
8. Bf1 e4 { And now White is forced to take the pawn. } 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Rxe4
d5 11. Re1
{ I like grabbing even more space and preventing d2-d4 from White. Castling is probably fine, but why not be a bit more ambitous? }
11... d4
{ We see in the mainlines of Re1 that one of White's biggest ideas is to gain space with d2-d4-d5. Now, we have beat him to the punch! I don't think Black is better, but he is certainly comfortably equal and can castle next. }
