11. b3
{ This is surely the most challenging move.   11.Nc3  d5=  Black is totally fine. }
11... Nb6 12. a4
{ White chases the knight around a bit, and makes sure to do so before Black can play d5, get his bishop off of c8, and his knight back to c8 and then d6. It looks a little awkward but Black is fine with accurate play. }
12... Nd5 13. c4 Ne7
{ The pin means White is unable to push d4-d5, therefore he cannot stop Black from playing d7-d5 himself. Black is very fine. }
