1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
c4 Ba6 9. b3 g6 10. g3 Bg7 11. Bb2 O-O 12. Bg2 Rae8
{ 12...Rfe8  This would beour repertoire. The positions are extremely similar of course. }
13. O-O Bxe5 14. Qxe5 Qxe5 15. Bxe5 Rxe5 16. cxd5 Bxf1 17. Kxf1 cxd5 18. Nc3 c6
19. Rd1
{ I quite like how Gozzoli handled the resulting endgame. His play was not perfect, but he knew to centralize his king and fight for the a5-a4 advance. That's all there really is to it- White's minor pieces lack any decent targets. }
19... Rb8 20. Bf3 a5 21. Na4 Rb4 22. Nc5 Re7 23. Rc1 g5
{ This felt unnecessary.   23...Kf8  I'd prefer just bringing the king to the center right away. }
24. h3 Kf8 25. Bg4 Ke8 26. Nd3 Rb5 27. Be2 Kd8 28. Nb2 Rb8 29. Rc5 Ra8
{ White's moves feel a bit aimless, and while Black could have reached the right coordination faster, he is playing with purpose. The king is coming to d6. }
30. Nd1 Kc7 31. Ne3 Kb6 32. Rc1 Re5 33. g4 h6 34. Bd3 Rh8 35. Be2 Re4
{ I like this move a lot. Black gets ready for a5-a4. } 36. Bd3 Rd4 37. Bf5 Kc7
38. Ke2 a4
{ Finally. White now is in serious trouble, as the rooks will soon be activated. }
39. bxa4 Rb8 40. Bc2 Rb2 41. Kf3 Rxa2
